hopobject.body: What do you want to do when you've finished? nopainpro.com The results of Curiosity’s first 100 days on Mars, published in the journal Science this week, also revealed the presence of a rock with a far more complicated chemical history than scientists expected to find on Mars. Curiosity is continuing its search for habitats that could have supported ancient microbial life. It already has found one suitable location inside an ancient slab of bedrock near the rover’s Gale Crater landing site.
